387
00:30:44,555 --> 00:30:45,624
Everybody all right?

388
00:30:45,765 --> 00:30:48,154
I saw him. It's that guy over there!

389
00:30:56,484 --> 00:30:58,679
Okay, so he was there last night.

390
00:30:58,861 --> 00:31:01,011
Debbie's gonna meet us
on the other side of the bridge.

391
00:31:15,712 --> 00:31:17,145
Yeah, Ben.

392
00:31:17,463 --> 00:31:19,818
"A few days in space. It'll be great.

393
00:31:20,717 --> 00:31:22,912
"What's the worst that could happen?"

394
00:31:27,056 --> 00:31:28,330
Hey, little guy.

395
00:31:30,435 --> 00:31:32,471
You're not afraid of me, are you?

396
00:31:38,234 --> 00:31:39,303
Perfect.

397
00:31:40,903 --> 00:31:42,018
Thanks.

398
00:31:56,461 --> 00:31:57,576
Hey!

399
00:31:59,130 --> 00:32:02,122
You think you've got problems?
You take a good look, pal.

400
00:32:03,468 --> 00:32:05,265
How bad could it be, right?

401
00:32:05,762 --> 00:32:07,514
I don't think you...

402
00:32:09,182 --> 00:32:12,777
Okay, pal. Take it easy.
No, don't go out there.

403
00:32:13,019 --> 00:32:15,487
Look, I said stop, you fruitcake!

404
00:32:15,688 --> 00:32:17,406
No. Come close.

405
00:32:18,149 --> 00:32:20,458
That's further. Come closer.

406
00:32:20,651 --> 00:32:22,801
I said, stop! No!

407
00:32:47,470 --> 00:32:48,744
Come here.

408
00:33:12,412 --> 00:33:14,846
All right, calm down.

409
00:33:16,666 --> 00:33:18,099
You wanna be scared?

410
00:33:18,251 --> 00:33:19,969
- Fine!
- No!

411
00:33:30,346 --> 00:33:32,098
Get back, everybody!

412
00:33:32,306 --> 00:33:35,059
Get back in your vehicle.
We'll tell you when you can go.

413
00:33:35,268 --> 00:33:38,340
- What do we do now?
- We're not going to get past these guys.

414
00:33:38,563 --> 00:33:39,882
But you could.

415
00:33:44,485 --> 00:33:47,045
Sorry about the truck, pal. Come on.

416
00:33:47,697 --> 00:33:50,450
A little help, here?
You wanna hit the button, sir?

417
00:33:50,867 --> 00:33:52,095
It's stuck.

418
00:33:53,828 --> 00:33:55,864
Sue, your clothes. Lose them.

419
00:33:56,664 --> 00:33:57,779
Right.

420
00:33:58,458 --> 00:34:00,130
This is so wrong.

421
00:34:08,593 --> 00:34:11,061
- Wow, you've been working out.
- Shut up!

422
00:34:13,139 --> 00:34:14,174
All right.

423
00:34:18,269 --> 00:34:19,987
All right, freeze!

424
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:21,799
Now just...

425
00:34:22,482 --> 00:34:24,916
Just put the man in the seat down.

426
00:34:26,235 --> 00:34:27,384
Do it!

427
00:34:32,659 --> 00:34:33,978
Any more great ideas?

428
00:34:34,118 --> 00:34:36,507
Why don't you strip down
and have a 100 people stare at you?

429
00:34:36,704 --> 00:34:38,422
- Sue.
- What?

430
00:34:43,044 --> 00:34:44,636
I'm gonna need therapy.

431
00:34:46,798 --> 00:34:48,754
Come on, let's get out of here.

432
00:34:50,677 --> 00:34:52,633
Excuse me. Coming through.

433
00:34:57,266 --> 00:35:00,417
All right, now just back away from him.

434
00:35:02,480 --> 00:35:05,313
And I want you to put your hands
on your head...

435
00:35:13,616 --> 00:35:15,049
954 approaching scene.

436
00:35:15,243 --> 00:35:17,154
I still can't believe you made me do that.

437
00:35:17,328 --> 00:35:19,637
We got through, didn't we? Just find Ben.

438
00:35:26,921 --> 00:35:28,798
Ben!

439
00:35:37,265 --> 00:35:38,380
Mum.

440
00:36:24,645 --> 00:36:25,998
Stay here, okay?

441
00:36:26,189 --> 00:36:27,417
I'm coming.

442
00:36:27,940 --> 00:36:28,975
Hold on.

443
00:37:12,068 --> 00:37:13,262
Hang on!

444
00:37:19,701 --> 00:37:20,736
I got you.

445
00:38:00,074 --> 00:38:02,542
<i>Get down on the ground. </i>

446
00:38:03,911 --> 00:38:05,822
<i>Get down on the ground now!</i>

447
00:38:11,210 --> 00:38:12,199
Ben.

448
00:39:26,077 --> 00:39:27,590
I swear to you...

449
00:39:28,371 --> 00:39:30,726
I will do everything in my power...

450
00:39:30,915 --> 00:39:33,190
until there is not a breath left in me.

451
00:39:35,003 --> 00:39:36,834
You're going to be Ben again.

452
00:39:47,223 --> 00:39:48,781
I told you I felt fine.

453
00:39:50,018 --> 00:39:51,531
Where are your ears?

454
00:39:55,064 --> 00:39:57,862
There are some folks outside
that want to talk to you.

455
00:39:58,067 --> 00:39:59,705
We're not going public with this.

456
00:39:59,861 --> 00:40:01,579
We're scientists, not celebrities.

457
00:40:01,738 --> 00:40:03,137
It's too late, son.

458
00:40:03,573 --> 00:40:04,608
Look.

459
00:40:05,700 --> 00:40:07,531
<i>... when a New York Fire Department</i>
<i>ladder truck... </i>

460
00:40:07,702 --> 00:40:08,691
See that?

461
00:40:08,828 --> 00:40:09,943
<i>... became part of the tragedy. </i>

462
00:40:10,079 --> 00:40:12,354
<i>But the rescue itself is not the story. </i>

463
00:40:12,540 --> 00:40:14,929
<i>One of the four stretched</i>
<i>to an amazing length... </i>

464
00:40:15,126 --> 00:40:18,323
That's what they're calling you.
"The Fantastic Four. "

465
00:40:18,546 --> 00:40:20,741
